git stash is like a temporary save button for your unfinished work.

Developers use git stash when they need to stop working on something but do not want to lose their changes.


Common reasons:
  
  You need to switch branches.
  
  You need to pull the newest code.
  
  You need to fix something urgent.
  
  Your work is not ready for a commit yet.

